Usage: createPGPin [-help] {-onDie {-selected | -net <netName>} [-width <float>] [-length <float>]} | {pgPinName [-net <netName>] [-geom <layerName> <llx> <lly> <urx> <ury>]} [-dir {bidi|input|output}]

-help                        # Prints out the command usage
<pgPinName>                  # PG pin name (string, optional)
-dir {bidi input output}     # Direction of pg pin. (enum, optional)
-geom <layerName> <llx> <lly> <urx> <ury>
                             # geometry (string, optional)
-length <float>              # Pin Length. Default is same as width
                             # (float, optional)
-net <netName>               # create PG pins on specific net
                             # (string, optional)
-onDie                       # create PG pins on die (bool, optional)
-selected                    # create PG pins on die for all selected stripes
                             # (bool, optional)
-width <float>               # Pin Width. Default is stripe width
                             # (float, optional)